A two-year-old boy who went missing from his home on Sunday was later found dead in the back seat of his grandfather's car with the windows and doors closed.

Hezekiah Brooks, two, disappeared on Sunday afternoon at 2.30pm in Pensacola, Florida. The toddler was found hours later on the floorboards of the car.

Attempts to resuscitate the child failed
 and he was pronounced dead. The Medical Examiner is currently 
investigating the cause of death but police believe there were no signs of foul play.

